{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/servicereference"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/ServiceReference"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockServiceReference","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/RevenueCatPaywallService"],"anchor":"Related-Documentation","title":"Related Documentation"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockServiceReference","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/UIComponentsReference"],"anchor":"Reference","generated":true,"title":"Reference"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" adapts "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCat.Purchases"},{"type":"text","text":" to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol that "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxPaywall.PaywallPlugin"},{"type":"text","text":" requires. It does one job: translate "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" into "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EntitlementSnapshot"},{"type":"text","text":" (defined by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxPaywall"},{"type":"text","text":") so the plugin can drive its state. Configuration of the RevenueCat SDK itself remains the caller’s responsibility."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For a step-by-step integration walkthrough, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". For the entitlement-mapping rules, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Library-target","type":"heading","text":"Library target"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Product: ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Import: ","type":"text"},{"code":"import SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Package.swift"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":[".product(name: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\", package: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\"),"]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Types","type":"heading","text":"Types"},{"level":3,"anchor":"docSwiduxRevenueCatPaywalldocumentationSwiduxRevenueCatPaywallRevenueCatPaywallService","type":"heading","text":"``doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/RevenueCatPaywallService``"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["public struct RevenueCatPaywallService: PaywallService {","    public init(","        entitlementID: String,","        permanentLicenseEntitlementID: String? = nil","    )","","    public func customerInfo() async throws -> EntitlementSnapshot","    public func customerInfoStream() -> AsyncStream<EntitlementSnapshot>","    public func restorePurchases() async throws -> EntitlementSnapshot","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Value type. Holds two "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":" identifiers and forwards every call to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purchases.shared"},{"type":"text","text":". Cheap to construct and pass into "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallPlugin"},{"type":"text","text":" — after "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatPaywall.configure"},{"type":"text","text":" has run. For production, wrap it in SwiduxPaywall’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ResilientPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" so a transient read failure at launch never gates a paid user as free."}]},{"level":4,"anchor":"Initializer","type":"heading","text":"Initializer"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["public init(","    entitlementID: String,","    permanentLicenseEntitlementID: String? = nil",")"]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"entitlementID","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — RevenueCat entitlement identifier that grants pro access. Surfaces as ","type":"text"},{"code":"EntitlementSnapshot.isPro","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when active.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"permanentLicenseEntitlementID","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — Optional secondary identifier for a lifetime \/ permanent entitlement. Surfaces as ","type":"text"},{"code":"EntitlementSnapshot.hasPermanentLicense","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when active. Pass ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if the app has no separate lifetime SKU.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Call "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/RevenueCatPaywall\/configure(apiKey:appUserID:userDefaults:logLevel:entitlementVerification:purchasesAreCompletedBy:storeKitVersion:)"},{"type":"text","text":" before constructing the service. The initializer preconditions on the SDK being configured — failing fast with a named fix instead of letting "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purchases.shared"},{"type":"text","text":" trap opaquely at first use. Previews and tests should construct "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MockRevenueCatPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"level":4,"anchor":"customerInfo-async-throws-%3E-EntitlementSnapshot","type":"heading","text":"`customerInfo() async throws -> EntitlementSnapshot`"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One-shot fetch. Calls "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purchases.shared.customerInfo()"},{"type":"text","text":" and maps the result."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Throws whatever the RevenueCat SDK throws ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ErrorCode.networkError"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".offlineConnectionError"},{"type":"text","text":", etc.). The plugin catches the error and dispatches "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".refreshFailed(message)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"level":4,"anchor":"customerInfoStream-%3E-AsyncStream%3CEntitlementSnapshot%3E","type":"heading","text":"`customerInfoStream() -> AsyncStream<EntitlementSnapshot>`"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Long-lived stream. Wraps "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purchases.shared.customerInfoStream"},{"type":"text","text":" and yields a new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EntitlementSnapshot"},{"type":"text","text":" for every change RevenueCat reports — purchase, refund, family-share update, sandbox renewal."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The stream finishes when the underlying RevenueCat stream finishes. The plugin’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".observeCustomerInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" effect normally keeps it alive for the duration of the session; cancel by cancelling the consuming "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task"},{"type":"text","text":", which terminates the stream and tears down the bridge."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The stream buffers only the newest snapshot: each yield is a complete entitlement state, so a slow consumer sees the latest value rather than replaying stale intermediate states."}]},{"level":4,"anchor":"restorePurchases-async-throws-%3E-EntitlementSnapshot","type":"heading","text":"`restorePurchases() async throws -> EntitlementSnapshot`"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Maps the result of a restore. Reads "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purchases.shared.purchasesAreCompletedBy"},{"type":"text","text":" live and branches: observer mode ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".myApp"},{"type":"text","text":") calls "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"syncPurchases()"},{"type":"text","text":", the default mode calls "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"restorePurchases()"},{"type":"text","text":". In observer mode the SDK’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"restorePurchases()"},{"type":"text","text":" can alias or transfer purchases between accounts, so the service uses "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"syncPurchases()"},{"type":"text","text":" automatically — no special-casing in your app code. Throws whatever the SDK throws on error."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The plugin’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".restorePurchases"},{"type":"text","text":" action wraps this call and dispatches "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".customerInfoUpdated"},{"type":"text","text":" on success or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".refreshFailed"},{"type":"text","text":" on error."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Entitlement-mapping","type":"heading","text":"Entitlement mapping"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For every "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" the service receives:"}]},{"rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Configuration"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isPro"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hasPermanentLicense"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"entitlementID"},{"type":"text","text":" active"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(next column)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"entitlementID"},{"type":"text","text":" inactive or missing"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(next column)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"permanentLicenseEntitlementID == nil","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"—","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"permanentLicenseEntitlementID","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" active","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"—","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"permanentLicenseEntitlementID"},{"text":" inactive or missing","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"—","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"type":"table","header":"row"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both flags are checked independently against the same "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerInfo"},{"type":"text","text":". A user with both active subscription and lifetime entitlements gets both flags set. See "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for the reasoning behind the truth table."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"}],"role":"article","title":"Service Reference","roleHeading":"Article"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"API reference for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatPaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" — the RevenueCat-backed "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" conformer that the paywall plugin consumes."}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall":{"type":"topic","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall","title":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","abstract":[{"text":"RevenueCat adapter for Swidux’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallPlugin"},{"type":"text","text":". Implements "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" against "},{"code":"Purchases.shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ships a controllable mock for previews and tests, and pairs with ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for drop-in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallView"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerCenterView"},{"type":"text","text":" presentation."}]},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/UIComponentsReference":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/UIComponentsReference","type":"topic","title":"UI Components Reference","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/uicomponentsreference","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"API reference for the "},{"code":"revenueCatPaywall","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"c